revision.text:
'''Antimonate minerals''' are those minerals containing the [[antimonate]] (SbO<sub>4</sub><sup>3−</sup>) anion group. Both the Dana<ref>[http://webmineral.com/danaclass.shtml Dana system, Webmineral]</ref> and the Strunz<ref>[http://webmineral.com/strunz.shtml Strunz system, Webmineral]</ref> mineral classifications place the antimonates in with the [[phosphate minerals]].

