[[Image:Hermannp1.jpeg|thumb|200px|right|Plate from ''Mémoire aptérologique'' by Jean-Frédéric Hermann]]
'''Jean-Frédéric Hermann''' (Strasbourg 1768–1793) was a [[France|French]] [[physician]] and [[naturalist]] mainly interested in [[entomology]].<ref>Guide des fonds patrimoniaux des bibliothèques d'Alsace  Daniel Bornemann - 1995 "On y trouve la collection de Jean Hermann (1738-1800), docteur en médecine et professeur d'histoire naturelle à Strasbourg, celle de Jean- Frédéric Hermann (1768-1793) son fils et celle de [[Frédéric-Louis Hammer]] (1762-1835), son gendre."</ref>

Son of [[Jean Hermann]], he continued the index of his father’s collection, illustrating some species. He studied the comparative anatomy of the mouthparts of insects and mites publishing ''Mémoire aptérologique'' with his son in law [[Frédéric-Louis Hammer]] in 1804.

